records.addlTxt:
The State files an Amended Information which amends the charge to 4th degree sexual assault, contrary to Section 940.225(3m) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge of 4th degree sexual assault.  Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Defendant is to comply with sex offender treatment if ordered by DOC;
3) No contact with M.O.S., her residence or any place she temporarily occupies;
4) No contact with any minors unless approved by the agent;
5) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
6) Maintain absolute sobriety;
7) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
8) Provide DNA sample;
9) Pay court costs;
10) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Defendant has credit for 1 day if revoked.
Minutes.
